cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the application of coresets to logistic regression, which is a problem in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also introduces a complexity measure for logistic regression, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of sensitivity sampling and comparison to state-of-the-art methods suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. Finally, the experiments conducted on real-world data could also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
